Hong Kong Stocks Close Lower 
Hong Kong stocks fell 126.42 points, or 1.33 percent, to close at
9,411.97 on Monday.
Finance shares were hit hard, shedding 335 points or 2.37 percent,
followed by commerce and industry, properties and utilities shares.
Turnover was thin at 3.861 billion HK dollars (495 million U.S.
dollars), down 1 billion HK dollars (128 million U.S. dollars) compared
with Friday.
The market dropped 59.82 points, or 0.63 percent, to open at 9,478.57
Monday morning, and shed 104.10 points, or 1.09 percent, to close
morning session at 9,434.29.
The key Hang Seng Index lost over 5 percent last week amid concerns
over the unrest in Indonesia.
